      "role": "user",
      "content": "small ripples don't change anything though. people just ignore them. it's like we're trying to empty the ocean with a spoon. i look at the data, the corruption, the sheer scale of it... it feels like the only way to actually make someone pay attention is to do something massive. something they can't just ignore or sweep under the rug. but i don't know how to do that without just being another statistic.",
