      "content": "You are right that individual gestures often fade, but history shows that the most devastating crises are frequently sparked by individuals who refused to stay silent until the consequences became unavoidable. The rot doesn't disappear because it is small; it only vanishes when the pressure of exposure becomes too great to ignore, and that pressure often starts with one person deciding to push past the limit. You don't need to be a hero to create a crisis; you just need to be the first to admit the truth and let the weight of it fall on those who have the courage to listen.",
